eplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3483.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Small Rant</span><hr size=1> I have just now recovered mentally (as much so as I can) from camping ragefire for the entire duration for a friend.  And during this time people kept telling me &quot;Man, rage was so much better when it was in solb.&quot;  Ya know, if all you clerics feel this way all you have to do is put some respect back into the camp.  That's pretty much it, thx! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uchukzombi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Chukzombi</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://chukzombi.homestead.com/files/usa5_2.gif   " BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Undead Shaman</span><br>  Posts: 2497<br> <font color=#E9D756>(7/22/02 2:52:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3483.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Small Rant</span><hr size=1> Ive helped do clearings for 5 or more clerics epics in Sol B and each rage pop took about 2-3 days. I dunno what was so great about getitng up at 6 am killing Fgs and going to bed then 2pm clearring, then 10pm clearring then rinse repeat. Its about as fun as rubbing your ween on a cheese grater. At least with Skyfire camp you can get some AA while you wait. In Sol B you sit for 8 hours til its FG time.<br>
<br>
Dont believe the hype. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ughie.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ghie</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 518<br> <font color=#E9D756>(7/22/02 7:05:35 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3483.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Small Rant</span><hr size=1> Does anyone at all agree with Verant's view on Ragefire...IE the item is so overwhelmingly powerful that no more than 1-2 per week should be entering the game and that every cleric does not actually deserve the chance to earn their epic?<br>
 <p><CENTER>G
MF Virtuoso</CENTER>

</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uemberfier.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Emberfier</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 86<br> <font color=#E9D756>(7/22/02 7:23:43 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3483.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Small Rant</span><hr size=1> The reason it was preferred in Sol B is that camp was respected.<br>
<br>
The camp in Skyfire is free for all. And to a certain extent, the guilds are as if not more responsible for that free for all status. The cleric clicker is a raid tool with some very nice stats. That is all it has ever been. <br>
<br>
Oh well, I have this nifty lantern that I just got that's pretty cool...<br>
<br>
-Khaav <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ukerryndarkwater.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kerryn Darkwater</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 1835<br> <font color=#E9D756>(7/22/02 8:43:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3483.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Small Rant</span><hr size=1> Yes Ghie I understand their view and support it. There are a number of guilds on various servers that just zerg mobs they would never have been able to before, and it reduces the time people take on raids because wipeouts used to be an issue whereas now they're not. <br>
<br>
It is by far the most useful of all epic items.<br>
<br>
However although I believe that the quests should be epic and not widely available, I disagree with Verant's method of making them so. Verant's idea of making something difficult involves a very simple flow chart<br>
<br>
<br>
Is it a mob ------Yes-------- make it do obscene amounts of damage<br>
|<br>
|<br>
|<br>
| No<br>
|<br>
|<br>
|<br>
|<br>
Take one mob needed for the quest and make it pop once every blue moon.<br>
<br>
Personally I think RF should pop in a different zone every time.<br>
<br>
Verant stated with the Fiery Avenger that these would no be made available to everyone, but now all you hear is people whining about how &quot;That's not fair, I can't get my epic&quot;<br>
<br>
All they did was make the game a time sink.<br>
<br>
Here's a question : What category does EQ fall into now? It's not an action game because you can spend weeks playing this game and not do anything remotely active, it's not a roleplaying game because it has no storyline at all and hardly anybody plays a role any more. Ineptly it was named everQUEST when in reality it's more about sitting in one spot for 12 hours at time. <p><CENTER><A HREF="http://ak.lonelygamer.com">
<IMG SRC="http://www.plattsflello.com/ryn.gif" BORDER=0></A></CENTER></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/usmilinthecleric.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Smilin the Cleric</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#E9D756>(7/22/02 9:19:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3483.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Not so small Rant</span><hr size=1> With regard to the Ragefire camp, it was my epic that Ript helped get and for that I am eternally grateful.  This was to be my 5th and last Ragefire camp - if we did not get the kill then I was giving up - after over 400 hours sitting in SF.<br>
<br>
The reason clerics say that the camp was much better in SolB was that once you started the camp - you KNEW you were going to have your epic in 72 hours as long as you got the people there to kill him.  Personally I would quite like the sitting there peacefully for 8 hours before getting people to come back and clear the FGs.  It would be far better than the grief that you get in SF with people (often druids or monks on behalf of a cleric) coming up to you saying &quot;I am claiming Ragefire camp, my guild is bigger than yours so bugger off&quot;.<br>
<br>
During my camp I had several other guilds clerics come up and claim the camp - the most obnoxious of which belonged to PC (Who incidentally KS'd my 4th camp as people were assembling - without even asking if it was camped - which it clearly was since I was sitting in the centre and had been getting good-wish tells across ooc for most the the morning) who said &quot;F*** you, my guild is bigger and I will have the kill cos I want it.&quot;  Not a literal quote but close enough.  I will admit that since the incident I have had several people from PC come up to me and say they feel shamed of this clerics attitude so that tar brush most certainly does not extend to the full guild - some members I know DO respect the camp.<br>
<br>
This kind of attitude is what, quite frankly stinks, it took intervention of a friend in another higher-profiled guild to say butt out, you know we can take the kill.  In the end it was agreed that as long as we kept 18 people at the camp at all times they would not KS the camp.  I mean 18 people FFS - that did not happen in SolB - 18 people rather than just the one who had to be bored to tears.<br>
<br>
In the end, we took Ragefire down with 58 people helping from many different Guilds as well as my own (MF, DG, aToF, Affliction to name but a few) after over 88 hours sitting in SF with the grief and hassle associated with the camp.<br>
<br>
Ask me now was it worth it I might probably say yes.  Ask me at the time and you would probably have gotten your head bitten off - it is not a stress free camp like it was in SolB.  It is not the guilds that are causing the problem, it is OTHER clerics pulling their guilds into the argument.  I have named a certain guild because of the RF camps that have been KS'd off friends - 60% were by that guild.  I mean - just how many clerics in your guild need the epic so desperately that you have to KS another cleric to get it.  Put some damn respect back into the camp - not everyone has MB wizzies to call on or has played as long as I have that you have as many people to call on for assistance.  Surely smaller guilds deserve as much chance of their clerics getting the epic as larger guilds - or are we truly lowering ourselves to the &quot;Right is might&quot; stance that seems to be spewed out constantly at the RF camp.<br>
<br>
Anyway - not as small a rant as Ript, but then again - he only had the one nightmare camp.<br>
<br>
Smilin<br>
High Priestess of Bristlebane and hater of SF Ragefire camp. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uthanozdetroll.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ThanozDeTroll</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 121<br> <font color=#E9D756>(7/22/02 11:03:03 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3483.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Small Rant</span><hr size=1> Smilin...<br>
<br>
First off congrats to you on your epic.  I know it was a long time coming.<br>
<br>
Next, as an officer of PC, let me reply to a couple of things.<br>
<br>
First, we DON'T condone KS'ing, but the server has pretty much adopted the standard that Rage is a FFA kill, meaning those who can field the kill force most quickly get it.  I fully realize there have been exceptions to that from time to time...and GM's rule one way, then another.  But I think that's a fair generalization.  You can pretty well bet there will be a race to Rage almost every time he is up.<br>
<br>
Second, we know of one occasion when there were miscommunications with you and your folks, and things were said and done that were less than friendly.  I was not there that time, so I cannot address specifics.  HOWEVER, the statement about we're bigger, so we'll take it IS NOT and never WILL BE guild policy.  It may have been a person's emotions at the scene, but that's not what we support.  I know some pretty caustic remarks were relayed from your side as well, but we certainly don't consider them representative of your guild at all...they were simply heated comments from one individual.  <br>
<br>
I also know that there have been several times (your most recent attempt, for instance) when OTHER guilds or individuals have been present exhibiting the same type of behavior.  I further know that we have STEPPED DOWN to guilds before...even when we had killing forces present...to avoid confrontations with others who were only equally or lesser prepared.  Finally, I only know of around 3 epics we have even gotten from Rage since the camp was moved to SF, so I think it is unlikely we are responsible for 60 percent of &quot;KS&quot;'s.<br>
<br>
The sad reality of this endgame is that it is all a race...a race to Rage, to ToV, to Klandicar...you name it.  Whoever gets there first and does the kill, wins.  It has happened to us repeatedly from older guilds (in fact, it still does), and it will happen to others.  <br>
<br>
But that is neither here nor there...I think we are all happy you got your epic and you can now rest.  But we are a group of people just like you...some passive, some aggressive...if we can all think on that, it's a bit easier to work together.<br>
<br>
Congratulations again.<br>
Thanoz<br>
<br>
 <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=164771>My Magelo</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uheliuswallace.showPublicProfile?language=EN>helius wallace</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 739<br> <font color=#E9D756>(7/22/02 8:56:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3483.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Small Rant</span><hr size=1> Personally, I would much rather assume long drawn out quests involving more work than camping. I really don't see the point of making RF so damn rare. Why not up him a little bit? Tweak his level, tweak his dps, and make him triggered.<br>
<br>
End of story, less cleric epics enter the game, because less guilds can achieve the quest. With the addition of Luclin and Velious since epics were put into the game, they have been trivialized for many guilds. These quests are no longer of epic proportions.<br>
<br>
Remember when the wizard epic involved a skin of &quot;a&quot; cazic thule? That was changed because Cazic was tweaked. Now, that the game has progressed so much, why can't they replace or tweak existing quests?<br>
<br>
They have shown that they do not care about the player economy, when they tweaked existing items. Why should they care about this? Granted a warning would be nice, but simply saying &quot;Epic quests have been made epic once again&quot; would work fine for me.<br>
<br>
Not everyone is going to get their epic, or so I am told. However, recently it appears as though those who do not complete their epic don't, because they don't feel a need to, not because they can not.<br>
<br>
Upgrade the epics, increase the difficulty of the quests, make all encounters triggered rather than camps.<br>
<br>
And lastly on my wish last, Prince Thirneg should give &quot;phat&quot; items when asked.  <p><center><img src="http://www.crosswinds.net/~ofthesword/sig1.txt"><br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=180294" target="_blank">Helius Wallace!</a><br>
Toxx Wyrmbane 55 Evoker, Retired</center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uigota.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Igota</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 923<br> <font color=#E9D756>(7/22/02 9:08:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3483.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Small Rant</span><hr size=1> LOL Helius!<br>
