</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/usmilinthecleric.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Smilin the Cleric</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#E9D756>(7/23/02 1:04:43 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3483.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Small Rant</span><hr size=1> I think you misunderstood my point about the 60% - I said that 60% of my friends that I have asked have had a RF KS'd or muscled in by PC.  I am not saying that PC is responsible for 60% of KS'ing on server, even you guys don't have THAT many clerics <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I personally feel that Ragefire should be a triggered spawn like the Druid epic and even be made a little harder if necessary.  At least then there could surely be no arguments over it - the one who triggered him is the one entitled to the heart.<br>
<br>
Another deplorable tactic, one used by certain other guilds, is to have a druid there (you wondered why they camp RF with a camp not a cleric??) and to kite the human form until re-enforcements get there.  In the rules of VI, the first person to engage the mob is the one awarded the kill in the event of a dispute.  This tactic is even worse in my opinion - at least KS'ing groups have the people there to take him down when they engage.<br>
<br>
I agree that words were said on either side during my last camp and I apologise - after 47 hours then a damn server reset and another 20 hours (24 hours a day camp) your temper gets a little flared up.  The slightest provovation is all that is needed - personally I just ignored everyone who was rubbing me the wrong way - bit my fingers rather than my tongue if you will.  For that I apologise.<br>
<br>
Anyway, nuff said<br>
<br>
Smilin<br>
High Priestess of Bristlebane<br>
